It's a lot but really there are only 3 catagories of thing being mentioned
1. Module name, it wants it as a prefix but I have it as SymTableList_x
instead. I did this because I didn't know the standard and now it would
be a lot to change the rest, however I know for next time.

2. Asserts, some things such as pvExtra and pvValue are allowed to be
null so this isn't an issue

3. Size, because I copy pasted the code since the hash code couldn't
refer to the list code, it is a long program. Had I made everything
myself, I would have had a seperate ADT for the linked list that
I used in the hash table.

